related_questions.question: Where is the biggest IMAX screen?
related_questions.snippet: The world's largest IMAX screen currently stands in Leonberg near Stuttgart, Germany and measures 38 by 22 m (125 by 72 ft). Until 2021, the largest operating IMAX screen was located within the Melbourne Museum in Melbourne, Australia, measuring 32 m × 23 m (105 ft × 75 ft).
related_questions.title: IMAX - Wikipedia

related_questions.question: Where is the largest IMAX screen in USA?
related_questions.snippet: The screen in the AMC Lincoln Square IMAX in New York City is 75.6 feet tall and 101 feet wide. The next largest in the U.S is AMC Metreon IMAX in San Francisco: 75.6 x 97.6 feet. The largest in the world is IMAX Theatre Melbourne in Australia: 76.1 x 102 feet. What is an IMAX film?

related_questions.question: Is DBOX or IMAX better?
related_questions.snippet: If you want an experience that brings you right into the middle of every scene, IMAX is the ultimate choice. It offers a larger curved screen with an expanded aspect ratio for select films, that lets audiences see up to 26 percent more picture.
